 Matter, is conquered, by Iccha Shakti, what more is l=\r\neft there to conquer?\n&gt; \n&gt;   Also, it can be noted that when avatars like R=\r\nama face difficulties in Physical body, like being hit by shakti in the war=\r\n, the only great remedy is to conquer Tamo-Guna itself like Mahaavatar Baba=\r\nji has done.\n&gt; \n&gt; regards,\n&gt; Aryama\n&gt; \n&gt; --- In vedic-wisdom@...=\r\nm, Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@&gt; wrote:\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Namaste Sir,\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; &gt; Where i=\r\ns the fascination for what one already has ?\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; The fascination is n=\r\not &quot;for what one already has&quot;, but for resisting changes in that physical f=\r\norm with time based on the natural order (niyati)!\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; Striving for p=\r\nhysical immortality as a great ideal can create such an unhealthy fascinati=\r\non that is not idealized in any scriptures.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; All scriptures, wheth=\r\ner it is Upanishads or Yoga Vaasishtham, say that you overcome your self-id=\r\nentification with the perishable body and identify with that which cannot b=\r\ne destroyed. Then you are liberated. After that, what happens to the body -=\r\n whether it remains invincible for a few millennia or for few million years=\r\n or forever or gets a cancer and perishies soon like in the case of Ramakri=\r\nshna Paramahamsa and Ramana Maharshi - does not really matter, because you =\r\nare not that body anyway.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; &gt; How do you know that this state is no=\r\nt achieved by actively pursuing it ?\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; (1) As I said, Yoga Vaasisht=\r\nham and other scriptures tell you to unidentify with the body to realize hi=\r\ngher realities. They do talk about higher states beyond samdhi, but never t=\r\nell you to think of the physical body as you attempt to realize.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; =\r\n(2) Saints/yogis who ascended to the immortal planes with their physical bo=\r\ndy (e.g. Sant Tukaram who was 